People always tend to see relations between states too one-sidedly. Like you hear "South Korea is a puppet state of America" and it sounds reasonable, but Sun Myung Moon literally got to pick the US president a few times. Bush literally recognized him as a deity in one interview.

Gene Wolfe has something similar in Book of The New Sun with Dr. Talos and Baldanders where the relation is ambivalent and at first it seems like a dumb bodyguard type henchman guy and a clever mastermind doctor but later it turns out that this is an optical illusion of sorts.

Alone looking at the League of Cambrai in the 16th century is enough to show just how ambivalent the relations between allies and enemies actually are. Today "allies" and "enemies" probably carry polar opposite definitions in most types of context. Similar with "vassalhoods" too.
